\begin{align*}
64^{1011} &= 256^{2022}
\end{align*}

Now, we need to find the tens digit of $256^{2022}$. We can do this by finding the pattern of the digits in the power of 2:

\begin{align*}
2^1 &= 2 \\
2^2 &= 4 \\
2^3 &= 8 \\
2^4 &= 16 \\
2^5 &= 32 \\
2^6 &= 64 \\
2^7 &= 128 \\
2^8 &= 256
\end{align*}

We can see that the tens digit repeats every 4 powers. Since $2022$ is divisible by 4, the tens digit of $256^{2022}$ will be the same as the tens digit of $256^4$:

\begin{align*}
\text{Tens digit of } 256^4 &= \text{Tens digit of } 16^4 \\
&= \text{Tens digit of } 102576 \\
&= 6
\end{align*}

Therefore, the tens digit of $81^{1011}$ is \boxed{6}.

